{{ja-kanjitab|くわ|yomi=kun}}

{{IPAchar|/kupa/}} → {{IPAchar|/kuɸa/}} → {{IPAchar|/kuwa/}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|-}}.  Found in the ''{{w|Man'yōshū}}'', completed some time after 759 CE.<ref name="MYS">{{RQ:Manyoshu|7|1357}}, text [http://jti.lib.virginia.edu/japanese/manyoshu/Man7Yos.html#1357 here]</ref>

Ultimate derivation unclear.  Definitely not related to {{cog|ko|뽕||mulberry tree}} or {{m|ko|오디||mulberry fruit}}, nor to {{cog|ain|テㇱマニ|tr=tesmani||mulberry tree}} or {{m|ain|ツレㇷ゚ニ|tr=turepni||mulberry tree}}.

Some theories suggest this might have originally been a compound.  Possible derivations may include:

* A shift from {{m|ja|蚕}}{{m|ja|葉|tr=kopa||silkworm + leaf}}
* A shift from {{m|ja|胡}}{{m|ja|葉|tr=kopa||non-Chinese people to the west of China + leaf}}, possibly referencing the origin of some mulberry species in central Asia
* A contraction of {{m|ja|食う|食ふ}}{{m|ja|葉|tr=kupu pa||eat + leaf}}, where ''kupu'' is the ancient reading of modern {{m|ja|食う|tr=kuu}}
